  "doc_id": "43040",
  "text": "However, the thin-client model has three critical drawbacks. First, some web objects may not be properly rendered, and dynamic web pages may not function correctly because what the browser shows to users are simply rendered images or preprocessed web pages [CITATION_1] . For example, an interactive feature of a web page written in a script language will not react to user inputs because the browser is ignorant of the existence of the script code. Moreover, reloading or zooming in/out a part of a web page is difficult to handle for the same reason. The interactivity of mobile applications is important in the future internet [CITATION_2] . Accordingly, the lack on supporting the interactivity can be an obstacle to a better web browsing experience on the mobile network.",
